Dreams and the memories of life are never motionlessâ€”just as the wind never stops blowing.

metadata.name: Jellies #19
metadata.description:
Shimmering beams of alluring moonlight compel the jellies to rise toward the surface.  On their way, their sinewy tentacles snare small fish swimming in schools, weaving throughout towers of kelp.

Immerse yourself in this 1990x1080 generative seascape created using p5js and the p5js library.  

Coding procedures used:
Recursions, stochastic randomness and noise, flow fields and vectored ellipses.

Press the Down Arrow to save a frame as a png.
Click or Tap the canvas to toggle full screen mode.

metadata.name: Iris Diffusion #15
metadata.description:
"Iris Diffusion" was born from the sheer enjoyment of the intricacies of eye irises. Using a combination of Perlin noise flows and human specific colour ranges, I was able to string together a widely accurate spectrum of human eye variations.

Hope you enjoy my first collection :)

Main Colours

12% green
16% brown
25% dark brown
15% hazel
32% blue

metadata.name: tr4ns4ctions #53
metadata.description:
Tr4ns4ctions is a series of real-time animations that use pixels to create an abstraction of the movement of values. The pixels are constantly rearranging, being transferred from offer to taker, liquify, appear and disappear. They are forming endless compositions, sometimes intransparent or with strange spins.

The level of abstraction has been set to a 2x pixel size and the color palette of the NES with 12 different color modes. 16 pixel patterns serve as the fundamental building blocks and a simplex noise field determines the direction of movement.

click || space => pause/unpause

View all tr4ns4ctions at https://tr4ns4ctions.com

Kim Asendorf, 2022

metadata.name: EcoPatterns #63
metadata.description:
This project is an invitation to see nature as an inspiring source through its complex and elegant patterns. The structures of a leaf, the symmetry of a flower, or the harmonious multicolored combinations can be inexhaustible resources for the mind of a generative artist eager to reproduce so much beauty around them.
Made entirely in p5.js

metadata.name: Tears of the Mountains #139
metadata.description:
The "Tears of the Mountains" is a generative art collection that showcases emotions ranging from tears of happiness to boundless optimism. Inspired by Edgar Payne, I infused my own creative perspective into this art piece, giving consideration to important components such as value, composition, the rule of thirds, and perspective.

This series was crafted with pure code using p5.js.

Created by Costa C. | OneRocket.nft

metadata.name: Planetarium #75
metadata.description:
Francesco Forcellini, November 2022, Milano, Italy.
Compositions of spheres made with grids, proportions, symmetries and  broken symmetries,  order and casualties.


To save an image with the size of the window press S once the image is fully rendered.
To save a Hi-Resolution image 6000px x 8000px press H and wait, the page will reload and start to render.
